<dl id="n09052b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09052b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09052b"> 52(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> drought famine <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09052b"><li>FW 539.36 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n09052b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n09052b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n09052b">MS BL 47482b-106</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:079 <a name="rA2yd" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rB0yd">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/rB0yd.htm#n09052b">Draft: III&sect;3B.0+</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Il tombe bien, en moyenne, un peu plus d&apos;eau dans la vall&eacute;e du Gange, de la Djamna jusqu&apos;&agrave; B&eacute;nar&egrave;s, que dans celle de l&apos;Indus, mais la quantit&eacute; de pluie qu&apos;elle re&ccedil;oit n&apos;est pas suffisante pour assurer les r&eacute;coltes: dans les bonnes ann&eacute;es, il est vrai, la fertilit&eacute; du sol y est au moins &eacute;gale &agrave; celle de l&apos;Egypte et de la M&eacute;sopotamie; aussi l&apos;Aryavarta oriental fut-il, de tout temps, une contr&eacute;e peupl&eacute;e au maximum, et, par suite, les <mark>s&eacute;cheresses et les famines</mark> devaient y &ecirc;tre au plus haut degr&eacute; meurtri&egrave;res. <font color="green">[It is a fact that, on average, a little more water falls in the Ganges Valley, and the Djamma Valley down as far as Benares, than in the Indus Valley. But the quantity of rain it receives is not enough to guarantee a harvest. It is true that in good years the fertility of the soil is at least equal to what is found in Egypt and Mesopotamia. Therefore, eastern Aryavarta has always been a region of maximum population and, as a result, droughts and famines must have been lethal to the highest degree there.]</font> <small> L&eacute;on Metchnikoff, <a name="LMCG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMCG"><cite title="source">La Civilisation et les grands fleuves Historiques</cite></a> (1889) 312</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
